acadena\'s</em> house was obviously not ideal for corporate worship, the <em>JSOS</em> initial members and leaders prayed for a larger area.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n With God\'s mercy and provision, <em>Delfin Tacadena</em>, the pastor\'s eldest brother, bought a lot with unfinished house in front of the original sight. <em>Brother Delfin</em> developed it and lent it to the church to become it\'s official church worship center.</p>\r\n<p>[/two_third_last]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_animate]</p>','History','','inherit','closed','closed','','317-revision-v1','','','2016-10-02 07:30:18','2016-10-02 07:30:18','',317,'http://localhost/jsos_wp/2016/10/02/317-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(327,1,'2016-10-02 07:39:47','2016-10-02 07:39:47','<p>[su_animate type=\"fadeInUp\"]</p>\r\n<p>The name <strong><em>JSOS</em> </strong>was not decided upon by the small group of Christian incorporators through haphazard thinking and careless discussion. Instead, the name came about as a result of deep individual and group prayers and meditation not only on the Bible but also on certain events preceeding the establishment of the church that bears the said name.<br />\r\n After much prayerful discussion that lasted months, the incorporators of the said group were one in testifying that the name, \" <strong><em>JESUS: Sovereign Overcoming Shepherd</em></strong> \" is God-given for the specific purposes He has stored for this church.</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n [su_tabs vertical=\"yes\" class=\"my-custom-tabs\"]<br />\r\n [su_tab title=\"Sovereign\"]</p>\r\n<p>[one_fifth]</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"mr-20 aligncenter wp-image-116 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/tbn_sovereign.jpg\" alt=\"Sovereign\" width=\"123\" height=\"130\" /></p>\r\n<p>[/one_fifth]</p>\r\n<p>[four_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>That God is sovereign does not take away the fact that He still has many enemies. In fact, we, Christians have many enemies ourselves beginning with the chief opponent himself, Satan. In the Bible, Satan has mobilized his demonic forces to oppose God\'s people in every possible way. With God\'s loving and sovereign permission, the devil uses problems, sicknesses, failures, other people and even nature and circumstances to overcome us. But praise God because Jesus overrules all of them! In fact, Satan has thrown everything to Jesus in his attempt to defeat our Great Shepherd. But JESUS walloped him repeatedly from the temptation in the wilderness ( Matthew 4:1-11 ) to his resurrection from the dead. (John 10:17,18; 20:1-31; Colossians 2;9-15) Jesus overruled demons, sicknesses, nature, evil plots and people in the course of His earthly life. He will continue to do so until the total annihilation of all His enemies. </p>\r\n<p>[/four_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]<br />\r\n [su_tab title=\"Overcoming\"]</p>\r\n<p>[one_fifth]</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"mr-20 aligncenter wp-image-114 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/tbn_overcoming.jpg\" alt=\"Overcoming\" width=\"118\" height=\"116\" /></p>\r\n<p>[/one_fifth]</p>\r\n<p>[four_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>That <em>God</em> is sovereign does not take away the fact that He still has many enemies. In fact, we, Christians have many enemies ourselves beginning with the chief opponent himself, Satan. In the Bible, Satan has mobilized his demonic forces to oppose God\'s people in every possible way. With God\'s loving and sovereign permission, the devil uses problems, sicknesses, failures, other people and even nature and circumstances to overcome us. But praise God because Jesus overrules all of them! In fact, Satan has thrown everything to Jesus in his attempt to defeat our Great Shepherd. But JESUS walloped him repeatedly from the temptation in the wilderness (<em> Matthew 4:1-11</em> ) to his resurection from the dead. (<em>John 10:17,18; 20:1-31;Colossians 2;9-15</em>) Jesus overruled demons, sicknesses, nature, evil plots and people in the course of His earthly life. He will continue to do so until the total annihilation of all His enemies.</p>\r\n<p>[/four_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]<br />\r\n [su_tab title=\"Shepherd\"]</p>\r\n<p>[one_fifth]</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"mr-20 aligncenter wp-image-115 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/tbn_shepherd.jpg\" alt=\"Shepherd\" width=\"112\" height=\"102\" /></p>\r\n<p>[/one_fifth]</p>\r\n<p>[four_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>This is an already widely accepted fact through out the universal body of Christian believers. Ever since <em>King David</em> wrote and sung,</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>\" The Lord is my shepherd; I shall not want \" ( Psalm 23:1 ),</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>God\'s people have learned to look up to the Lord as the shepherd who leads them in life. When <em>JESUS</em> became a man, He declared,</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>\" I am the good Shepherd. The good shepherd lays down his life for his sheep . . . I know my sheep pand my sheep know me-just as the Father knows me and I know the Father-I lay down my life for the sheep. \" ( John 10:11-15 )</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>As our shepherd, Jesus loves us and provides for our needs consistently.</p>\r\n<p>[/four_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_tab]<br />\r\n [/su_tabs]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_animate]</p>','Truth Behind Its Name','','publish','closed','closed','','truth-behind-its-name','','','2016-10-07 05:11:15','2016-10-07 05:11:15','',61,'http://localhost/jsos_wp/?page_id=327',0,'page','',0),(328,1,'2016-10-02 07:39:47','2016-10-02 07:39:47','<p>The name <strong><em>JSOS</em> </strong>was not decided upon by the small group of Christian incorporators through haphazard thinking and careless discussion. Instead, the name came about as a result of deep individual and group prayers and meditation not only on the Bible but also on certain events preceeding the establishment of the church that bears the said name.<br />\r\n After much prayerful discussion that lasted months, the incorporators of the said group were one in test