-30\">The dream is to be able to host <strong><em>Bible Art Exhibit</em></strong>  locally that is readily accessible to each person who thirsts for the <em>Word of God.  </em>The dream is to have our own <em>Recording Studio </em>for creating <em>Gospel Songs </em>to reach people across the globe.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n If you have the passion to help us with this vision, don\'t hesitate to contact us.  God bless you!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>[/two_fifth]</p>\r\n<p>[three_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>[su_gmap address=\"305 rainbow avenue rainbow village angono rizal philippines\"]</p>\r\n<p>[/three_fifth_last]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_animate]</p>','Location','','inherit','closed','closed','','82-revision-v1','','','2016-10-07 05:04:56','2016-10-07 05:04:56','',82,'http://localhost/jsos_wp/2016/10/07/82-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(449,1,'2016-10-07 05:05:33','2016-10-07 05:05:33','<p>[su_animate type=\"fadeInUp\"]</p>\r\n<p>[one_third]</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-113 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/h3-300x168.jpg\" alt=\"JSOS\" width=\"300\" height=\"168\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-87\" src=\"http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/h1-300x168.jpg\" alt=\"h1\" width=\"300\" height=\"168\" /></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-112 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost/jsos_wp/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/h2-300x168.jpg\" alt=\"?????\" width=\"300\" height=\"168\" /></p>\r\n<p>[/one_third]</p>\r\n<p>[two_third_last]</p>\r\n<p>The <em><strong>JSOS Christian Church</strong></em> had its obscure beginning way back in 1992.</p>\r\n<p>That was after <em>Pastor Jose C. Tacadena</em> and his family (composed of wife <em>Adelia</em>, and children <em>Jihrael</em> and <em>Jehannah</em> ) left Manila where they had lived and ministered for six years. Having arrived in <em>Angono, Rizal </em>where his parents live, the couple was encouraged to hold regular Bible studies there.</p>\r\n<p>The initial attendees were composed of that extended family ( parents <em>Domingo</em> and <em>Maria,</em> sisters <em>Lydia, Perla, </em><em>Rose</em> and <em>Tess,</em> and older brother <em>Romeo</em> and his wife sis. <em>Aida</em> ), and a few faithful friends and co-workers in <em>Christ</em> from their previous Manila ministry. ( sisters <em>Adah</em> and <em>Allaine Nicolas,</em> Baby and <em>Berna Aquino,</em> and <em>Jimmy Manarang</em> ).</p>\r\n<p>Later on, the turn of events confirmed God\'s leading to establish a local church right in Rainbow Village.  The house of<em> Domingo Tacadena</em> served as its house church then.</p>\r\n<p>The name <em><strong>JESUS; SUPREME OVERRULING SHEPHERD </strong><strong>C</strong>HRISTIAN </em>church was chosen after much prayer and deliberation among the original incorporators primarily as a testimony of God\'s overruling supremacy in character and deeds, His overruling ability over all creations and principalities, and his unending personal love for every one, particularly for His sheep.</p>\r\n<p>After five months of holding mere home Bible studies at the said house, the small group of believers finally had their first Sunday Morning Worship Service on <em>June 28, 1992.  </em>Since <em>Tacadena\'s</em> house was obviously not ideal for corporate worship, the <em>JSOS</em> initial members and leaders prayed for a larger area.<br />\r\n <br />\r\n With God\'s mercy and provision, <em>Delfin Tacadena</em>, the pastor\'s eldest brother, bought a lot with unfinished house in front of the original sight. <em>Brother Delfin</em> developed it and lent it to the church to become it\'s official church worship center.</p>\r\n<p>[/two_third_last]</p>\r\n<p>[/su_animate]</p>','History','','inherit','closed','closed','','317-revision-v1','','','2016-10-07 05:05:33','2016-10-07 05:05:33','',317,'http://localhost/jsos_wp/2016/10/07/317-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(450,1,'2016-10-07 05:06:28'